<text id="02-output-contract" title="confidence-thresholded-cascade Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for cheap-model answer, strong-model answer, and the cascade-level telemetry payload.</summary>

  <section title="Cheap model schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$id": "confidence-thresholded-cascade/cheap-answer",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["reasoning", "answer", "confidence_0_to_1", "requires_escalation"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "reasoning":             {"type": "string", "maxLength": 1500},
    "answer":                {"type": ["string", "null"]},
    "confidence_0_to_1":     {"type": "number", "minimum": 0.0, "maximum": 1.0},
    "requires_escalation":   {"type": "boolean"}
  }
}
    ]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Strong model schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$id": "confidence-thresholded-cascade/strong-answer",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["reasoning", "answer"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "reasoning": {"type": "string"},
    "answer":    {"type": "string"}
  }
}
    ]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Cascade decision (telemetry payload)">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$id": "confidence-thresholded-cascade/decision",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["used_model", "cheap_confidence", "escalated", "answer"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "used_model":       {"enum": ["cheap", "strong", "third"]},
    "cheap_confidence": {"type": "number", "minimum": 0.0, "maximum": 1.0},
    "escalated":        {"type": "boolean"},
    "answer":           {"type": "string"}
  }
}
    ]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Good example (valid cheap-model output)">
    <example type="good">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "reasoning": "The ticket mentions a charge of $19.99 with no associated subscription; billing category fits.",
  "answer": "billing",
  "confidence_0_to_1": 0.91,
  "requires_escalation": false
}
      ]]></code>
      <note>Reasoning first, confidence calibrated, IDK flag explicit. Accepted at threshold 0.85.</note>
    </example>
  </section>

  <section title="Bad example (invalid)">
    <example type="bad">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "answer": "billing",
  "confidence": 0.91
}
      ]]></code>
      <note>Wrong field name (`confidence` vs `confidence_0_to_1`), no reasoning, no IDK flag. Validator rejects.</note>
    </example>
  </section>

  <section title="Allowed transformations">
    <list>
      <item>Round `confidence_0_to_1` to 2 decimals.</item>
      <item>Map enum-style `answer` strings to canonical lower-snake-case for the downstream switch.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section title="Self-check checklist">
    <list>
      <item>Cheap schema has `reasoning` BEFORE `confidence_0_to_1`.</item>
      <item>`requires_escalation` is a required field, not optional.</item>
      <item>Strong schema has no confidence field.</item>
      <item>Telemetry payload's `used_model` enum is exhaustive.</item>
    </list>
  </section>
</text>
